<heading id="F77A81AAFF9C5204FF6EFF14FBBCCAD6" bold="true" box="[151,1071,153,180]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" reason="1">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FF6EFF14FBBCCAD6" bold="true" box="[151,1071,153,180]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
Key to the Colombian species of 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FF9C5204FDD6FF17FBBCCAD6" authority="Lepeletier, 1841" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[559,1071,153,180]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Schonnherria">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FDD6FF17FD0CCAD1" bold="true" box="[559,671,153,180]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Xylocopa</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FD49FF17FCCBCAD1" bold="true" box="[688,856,153,180]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Schonnherria</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="C81C4B37FF9C5204FC90FF17FBBCCAD6" author="Lepeletier, A. L. M." box="[873,1071,153,179]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" refId="ref32004" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. (1841) Histoire Naturelle des Insectes. Vol. 2. Hymenopteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret, Paris, 680 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9005" type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier, 1841</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFF6FFF67CA9E" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" box="[151,244,225,251]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Females</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E497654DFF9C5204FF6EFE8CFA0FCF82" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" type="key">
<keyStep id="17792E63FF9C5204FF6EFE8CFA0FCB37" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFE8CFA0FCB72" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" box="[151,1436,258,280]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFE8CFA0FCB72" box="[151,1436,258,280]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
1. Labrum with a distinct, large, single capitate tubercle approximately as large as median ocellus (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FB87FE8CFB2BCB72" box="[1150,1208,258,280]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1913,1938]" captionTargetBox="[167,1423,321,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,309,1888]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Examples of structural characters that are useful for species identification. Comparison of vertex punctation (Figs. 1 and 2). Comparison of the color of hairs on hind basitarsus (Figs. 3 and 4). Comparison of pubescence on T3–T5 (Figs. 5 and 6). Comparison of labrum shape (Figs. 7 and 8). Comparison of upper interocular distance (Figs. 9 and 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887578" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887578/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
)................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFEAEFA0FCB37" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFEAEFA0FCB37" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
- Labrum with three tubercles with similar size or longitudinally elongated median tubercle and two small sublateral tubercles (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FF10FEB3FEB1CB36" box="[233,290,317,339]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1913,1938]" captionTargetBox="[167,1423,321,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,309,1888]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Examples of structural characters that are useful for species identification. Comparison of vertex punctation (Figs. 1 and 2). Comparison of the color of hairs on hind basitarsus (Figs. 3 and 4). Comparison of pubescence on T3–T5 (Figs. 5 and 6). Comparison of labrum shape (Figs. 7 and 8). Comparison of upper interocular distance (Figs. 9 and 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887578" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887578/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
)............................................................................................. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="17792E63FF9C5204FF6EFED4FA0FCBA2" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFED4FA0FCBE9" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFED4FA0FCBE9" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
2(1). Clypeus, paraocular area, gena and lateral sides of T3 and T4 with whitish hairs (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FC14FED4FBBBCB15" box="[1005,1064,346,368]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1913,1938]" captionTargetBox="[167,1423,321,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,309,1888]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Examples of structural characters that are useful for species identification. Comparison of vertex punctation (Figs. 1 and 2). Comparison of the color of hairs on hind basitarsus (Figs. 3 and 4). Comparison of pubescence on T3–T5 (Figs. 5 and 6). Comparison of labrum shape (Figs. 7 and 8). Comparison of upper interocular distance (Figs. 9 and 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887578" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887578/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); T2 and T3 with short hairs (0.2–0.4x OD); distinct bluish or greenish highlights on metasoma...................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFE1BFA0FCBA2" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFE1BFA0FCBA2" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
- Pubescence ferruginous or black (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FDD2FE1BFDF5CBCE" box="[555,614,405,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1913,1938]" captionTargetBox="[167,1423,321,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,309,1888]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Examples of structural characters that are useful for species identification. Comparison of vertex punctation (Figs. 1 and 2). Comparison of the color of hairs on hind basitarsus (Figs. 3 and 4). Comparison of pubescence on T3–T5 (Figs. 5 and 6). Comparison of labrum shape (Figs. 7 and 8). Comparison of upper interocular distance (Figs. 9 and 10)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887578" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887578/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); T2 and T3 with short hairs barely noticeable (0.1x OD), nearly glabrous; weak (almost absent) bluish and greenish highlights on metasoma..................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="17792E63FF9C5204FF6EFE41FA0EC83F" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFE41FA0FC87A" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFE41FA0FC87A" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
3(2). Black hairs on T1 and T2 and yellowish hairs on T3–T6 and S4–S6; metasomal terga dark brown to black; head, legs and mesoscutum with bluish metallic highlights, greenish on mesoscutellum and metasoma (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FBEFFE63FB1AC866" box="[1046,1161,493,515]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–42" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,645,1912]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1435,633,1919]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 39–42. Female of Xylocopa (Schonnherria) metallica Smith, 1874. Fig. 39. Frontal view. Fig. 40. Detail of metasomal terga. Fig. 41. Dorsal habitus. Fig. 42. Lateral habitus. Scale bar 4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887594/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs. 39–42</figureCitation>
)................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FF9C5204FB99FD84FA0FC87A" authority="Smith, 1874" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1874" box="[1120,1436,522,544]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FB99FD84FA0FC87A" bold="true" box="[1120,1436,522,544]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FB99FD84FA8EC845" bold="true" box="[1120,1309,522,544]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Xylocopa metallica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C81C4B37FF9C5204FADAFD84FA0FC87A" author="Smith, F." box="[1315,1436,522,544]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" pagination="247 - 302" refId="ref34236" refString="Smith, F. (1874) Monograph of the genus Xylocopa Latr. Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 22, 247 - 302. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00168. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Smith, 1874</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFDA6FA0EC83F" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFDA6FA0EC83F" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
- Black hairs on metasomal disc with few whitish hairs on T4; metasomal terga black with distinct reddish brown-gold area distally, denser on T2 and T3; integument with bluish highlights on all tagmata (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FC1DFDCBFBC5C83E" box="[996,1110,581,603]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,607,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,597,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–14. Female of Xylocopa (Schonnherria) auriventris n. sp. (holotype) Fig. 11. Frontal view. Fig. 12. Detail of metasomal terga. Fig. 13. Dorsal habitus. Fig. 14. Lateral habitus. Scale bar 4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887580" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887580/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs. 11–14</figureCitation>
).... 
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FB6BFDCAFA0EC83F" bold="true" box="[1170,1437,580,602]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FF9C5204FB6BFDCAFAF3C83F" authority="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo, 2020" authorityName="Villamizar &amp; Fernández &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2020" box="[1170,1376,580,602]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auriventris" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FB6BFDCAFAF3C83F" bold="true" box="[1170,1376,580,602]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Xylocopa auriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="85CA57AFFF9C5204FA9FFDCBFA0EC83F" box="[1382,1437,581,602]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="17792E63FF9C5204FF6EFDECFA0FC96F" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFDECFA0FC8D7" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFDECFA0FC8D7" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
4(2) Metasoma dark brown to black with reddish brown areas on T1–T4; slightly bluish highlights on mesoscutum, tegula and mesoscutellum, without metallic reflections on head, legs and metasoma; pubescence predominantly ferruginous to black; wings dark brown with blue and violet iridescence (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FD6DFD13FC94C8D7" box="[660,775,668,691]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–62" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[159,1422,641,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1435,633,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 59–62. Female of Xylocopa (Schonnherria) simillima Smith, 1854. Fig. 59. Frontal view. Fig. 60. Detail of metasomal terga. Fig. 61. Dorsal habitus. Fig. 62. Lateral habitus. Scale bar 4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887606" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887606/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs. 59–62</figureCitation>
)............................ 
<taxonomicName id="6B8D4D45FF9C5204FBA6FD12FA0FC8D7" authority="Smith, 1854" authorityName=": Smith" authorityYear="1854" box="[1119,1436,668,690]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Xylocopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simillima">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FBA6FD12FA0FC8D7" bold="true" box="[1119,1436,668,690]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="9EF9EAD4FF9C5204FBA6FD12FA8EC8D7" bold="true" box="[1119,1309,668,690]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Xylocopa simillima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C81C4B37FF9C5204FADAFD12FA0FC8D7" author="Smith, F." box="[1315,1436,668,690]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336" pagination="199 - 465" refId="ref34185" refString="Smith, F. (1854) Apidae. In: Catalogue of hymenopterous insects in the collection of the British Museum. Part II. British Museum, London, pp. 199 - 465. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8766" type="book chapter" year="1854">Smith, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC3236C6FF9C5204FF6EFD34FA0FC96F" blockId="35.[151,1437,225,1512]" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
<keyLead id="177C95F3FF9C5204FF6EFD34FA0FC96F" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">
- Metasoma entirely black; bluish to violet highlights on head and legs and weak greenish on mesoscutellum and metasoma; pubescence predominantly black; wings dark brown with green iridescence apically and violet basally (
<figureCitation id="34B62A43FF9C5204FB3AFD59FAA6C888" box="[1219,1333,727,749]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–18" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1493,1518]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,189,1457]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1435,181,1467]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 15–18. Female of Xylocopa (Schonnherria) dimidiata Latreille, 1809. Fig. 15. Frontal view. Fig. 16. Detail of metasomal terga. Fig. 17. Dorsal habitus. Fig. 18. Lateral habitus. Scale bar 4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3887582" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3887582/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="336">Figs. 15–18</figureCitation>
).............................................................................. 
